). The final concentration of forward and reverse primers was 900 nM. The Applied Biosystems 7500 fast real-time PCR system (Thermo Fisher Scientific, Foster City, CA, USA) was used to estimate the numbers of biofilm-forming bacteria via a calibration curve method. The calibration curve was prepared using Streptococcus mutans ATCC 25175 genomic DNA.
